&lt;h2&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE APPLY FOR THIS VACANCY VIA CGL (CHANGE GROW LIVE) WEBSITE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;://careers-changegrowlive.icims.com/jobs/2693/health-and-wellbeing-nurse/job?mode=view&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Change, Grow, Live Manchester provide an integrated Alcohol and Drug service for the city of Manchester. We are looking to recruit a dynamic nurse with a passion for working with people who use substances to join our multi-disciplinary team. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supported by the Lead Nurse you will be an integral member of a multi-disciplinary team within Manchester.  You will support and deliver interventions to promote optimal health and wellbeing for the people who use our service including comprehensive alcohol assessments, health and wellbeing assessments blood borne virus screening, and support the team in the development and delivery of interventions to improve health. Case management of people with coexisting conditions will also be part of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; You will be a registered nurse with relevant skills, knowledge and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
